ak.'s "Henry VIII" and Inchbald-Kotzebue's "Lovers' Vows". Am anticipating my students' surprise when I tell them that they will have to read all that too in order to appreciate Jane. My plan is to teach my 150 students to read books, not just to get away with a "general" idea and a vague hash of "influences", "background", "human interest" and so forth. But this means work.1

